<Author>BangkokNegotiator
<Content>Nice hotel but a bit far from downtown We stayed at this hotel for 3 nights in December 2008. The hotel has ok lobby service and very good restaurant. We were there for a working/sight seeing trip. In the cold of the winter, the room was nice, very clean and warm. Seems like a new hotel to us, or may be it was renovated. What we really liked was the breakfast. Better than what we expected, actually, it was very good with good service. Only complaint maybe that it is a good 30 minutes from the main shopping street by train (cost only 2.6euros). But this is not really a problem for me as I travel a lot in Europe and best way to save is to get a hotel that is a bit far away. If you have more budget, then getting a downtown hotel would be better. 
